data.description:
1: Vitalik released a minimalist L1 privacy roadmap to enhance the privacy of Ethereum users;
2: The social application Towns completed a $10 million Series B financing, led by A16z;
3: The Ethereum Foundation transferred 1,000 ETH again, which may be used for grants;
4: Plastic Labs completed a $5.35 million pre-seed round of financing, led by Variant and others;
5: An early Ethereum ICO participant recharged 664 ETH to Kraken again, and sold 4,180 ETH in April;
6: Morpho responded to the front-end vulnerability: the update has been rolled back, and the security of user funds is not affected;
7: The total net outflow of Bitcoin spot ETF yesterday was 150 million US dollars, and the total net outflow of Ethereum spot ETF yesterday was 38.7929 million US dollars;
8: Perhaps affected by the formal abolition of the IRS DeFi broker rules, CRV briefly broke through 0.6 USDT;
9: CryptoQuant analyst: If Bitcoin fails to break through the $84,000 resistance level, it may consolidate around $80,000 in the short term;
10: Greeks.live: It is expected that the trade war and tariff war have not ended yet, and market uncertainty will continue for a long time;
11: New York Attorney General urged Congress to ban pension funds from investing in cryptocurrencies;
12: A newly created wallet absorbed more than 9,600 ETH 7 hours ago.
